# Data Visualisation


#Subscription type vs Subscription costs of Netflix in South Africa, United States and United Kingdom     
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 6))
selected_countries = ['South Africa', 'United States', 'United Kingdom']
filtered_data = Netflix_subscriptions.loc[Netflix_subscriptions['Country'].isin(selected_countries)].reset_index(drop=True)
analyzed_data = filtered_data[['Country', 'Cost Per Month - Basic ($)', 'Cost Per Month - Standard ($)', 'Cost Per Month - Premium ($)']]

n = 1
for col in selected_countries:
    plt.subplot(1, 3, n)
    country_data = analyzed_data.loc[analyzed_data['Country'] == col]
    melted_data = country_data.melt(id_vars='Country', var_name='Subscription Type', value_name='Subscription Cost')
    sns.barplot(y='Subscription Type', x='Subscription Cost', data=melted_data)
    plt.title(col)
    plt.yticks(rotation=80)
    n= n+1 
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
